  "query": "2024 peak demand all US ISOs CAISO ERCOT MISO ISO-NE NYISO PJM SPP comparison",
  "num_results": 8,
  "results": [
    {
      "url": "https://www.ercot.com/static-assets/data/news/content/a-peak-demand/2024/all-time-records.htm",
      "title": "2024 Peak Demand Records",
      "text": "2024 Peak Demand Records\n\n# 2024 Peak Demand Records\n\nLast updated: Nov 18, 2025\n\n#### November 2024\n\nPrevious Peak: 56,535 MW set 11/08/2023\n\n| Month | Demand (MW) |\n| --- | --- |\n| November 4 | 60,958 |\n| November 3 | 58,229 |\n\n#### October 2024\n\nPrevious Peak: 71,234 MW set 10/04/2023\n\n| Month | Demand (MW) |\n| --- | --- |\n| October 3 | 72,550 |\n| October 1 | 71,687 |\n\n#### May 2024\n\nPrevious Peak: 71,645 MW set 05/31/2022\n\n| Month | Demand (MW) |\n| --- | --- |\n| May 27 | 77,139 |\n| May 26 | 73,756 |\n| May 25 | 73,749 |\n| May 24 | 72,695 |\n| May 20 | 72,261 |\n\n#### April 2024\n\nPrevious Peak: 60,995 MW set 04/03/2023\n\n| Month | Demand (MW) |\n| --- | --- |\n| April 30 | 64,003 |\n| April 29 | 63,151 |\n| April 18 | 62,618 |\n\n#### January 2024\n\nPrevious Peak: 65,915 MW set 01/17/2018\n\n| Month | Demand (MW) |\n| --- | --- |\n| January 16 | 78,349 |\n| January 15 | 76,340 |\n| January 14 | 70,982 |\n\n#### 2024 Winter All-Time Records\n\nPrevious Peak: 74,525 MW set on 12/22/2023\n\n| Month | Demand (MW) |\n| --- | --- |\n| January 16 | 78,349 |\n| January 15 | 76,340 |\n\nHow many homes can 1 MW power?\n\n1 MW is enough to serve about 250 residential customers during ERCOT peak hours.\n\nWhere to find records\n\nCurrent official records can be found in the Demand tab in the Demand and Energy Report on Helpful Resources page. The numbers for the most recent months may change slightly as additional settlements passes are completed.\n\nHow records are set\n\nFor a demand record, ERCOT use the integrated system load for the full hour. ERCOT does not count instantaneous loads for demand records. The unofficial demands reported during, or just after, an operating day are preliminary. The numbers may change slightly as the data goes through the settlement process. After a final settlement pass occurs, after several months, the numbers are set and become official.\n\nHave a question?",
